Precinct-level Turnout and Vote-Share Model

Source: R/forecast.R
forecast_prec.Rd

Precinct-level Turnout and Vote-Share Model

Usage

forecast_prec(
  data,
  cands,
  turn,
  obs,
  obs_turn,
  weights = NULL,
  ctrl_form = ~1,
  prior_turn,
  prior_cands,
  prior_n_turn,
  prior_n_cands,
  draws = 1000
)

Arguments

data

A wide-format data frame

cands

A column specifying the vote counts.

turn

A column specifying the turnout counts.

obs

An indexing vector speciyfing whether each row is observed for turnout purposes.

weights

Optional weights for each observation.

ctrl_form

A formula specifying the control variables for both turnout and vote share models.

prior_turn

Prior on each precinct's turnout

prior_cands

Priors on each precinct's vote share for each candidate.

prior_n_turn

Effective total sample size for the turnout prior.

prior_n_cands

Effective total sample size for the vote share prior. Can be a single number or one number per candidate.

draws

Number of posterior draws to generate.

Value

A list with the model fits and prior and posterior draws for the precincts and the overall turnout and vote share.

Examples

data(nyc)
nyc$other = 1 - nyc$mamdani
nyc$other_prim = 1 - nyc$prim25_cvr_top_m

forecast_prec(
    data = nyc,
    cands = c(mamdani, other),
    turn = total,
    obs = obs < 0.25,
    obs_turn = obs < 0.25,
    ctrl_form = ~ log_s(votes_total_21) + prim25_cvr_top_m + p_white,
    prior_turn = votes_total_21,
    prior_cands = c(prim25_cvr_top_m, other_prim),
    prior_n_turn = 2,
    prior_n_cands = 2
)
